title: Independent candidate Faisal Khan wins PK-52 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): The Independent candidate Faisal Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-52, Swabi-IV by securing 42,269 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party (ANP) candidate Tauseef Ijaz who bagged 23,317 votes.
Voters turnout remained 40.56 percent.
